{
  "stem": "2522.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not a terrorist Zionism, but a Zionism that wanted to create a State of Israel and create a non-alienated Jewish state where anti-Semitism and the long diaspora could be terminated in, in freedom, and so the Jews could start building their own existence.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I vaguely remember, at the age of seven, one of the big ideological props of Hashomer Hatzair was a so-called Borochov Pyramid.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know whether you remember this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's, that's part of the lore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Borochov Pyramid show that every nation, every group of people built a state based on workers and, and, and head tradespeople just at the, the pinnacle.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, it was a socialist, kind of a worker-state orientation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Hashomer Hatzair view was that part of the reason why Jews were so alienated and, and also subject to anti-Semitism that their social structure made them especially vulnerable in an environment because Jews were basically an inverted pyramid.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the top of the Jews were the tradesmen and the innkeepers, who were hated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was no working class to support it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Betar-- there was a Betar and an Irgun organization.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, you, you name it, we had it in Trencin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, [LAUGHS] there was just a handful of Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were at least as many factions as there were Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This may be an exaggeration, but nevertheless.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there was a very strong Betar group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The, the, the Betar group were, were older.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were in their 20s.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they wore jackboots.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were black boots just like the storm troopers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they, they try to, to acquire arms and prepare themselves for, for, for aggressive takeover of Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
